Methods passing this selection stage were tested in a singleplex assay in a primer/probe concentration titration experiment (five primer/probe concentration combinations) using positive reference materials specific for the virus under analysis (Table 1
). Methods that performed well (i.e., positive reaction on the specific reference materials and no reaction on the negative control, lowest quantification cycle (Cq) value with lowest primer/probe concentration) were combined into a two-plex assay per virus (acceptance criterion: similar performance as the singleplex) and then into the final four-plex assay. The procedure followed is explained in Figure 1
.
